Name: SFN
ToolTip: System Frame Number, Value: 0-1023

Name: Slot
ToolTip: Value: 0-319

Name: nPDUs
ToolTip: Number of PDUs that are included in this message. All PDUs in the message are numbered in order. Value 0-255

Name: RachPresent
ToolTip: Indicates if a RACH PDU will be included in this message. 0: no RACH in this slot 1: RACH in this slot

Name: nULSCH
ToolTip: Number of ULSCH PDUs that are included in this message. Value: 0 - 255

Name: nULCCH
ToolTip: Number of ULCCH PDUs that are included in this message. Value: 0 - 255

Name: nGroup
ToolTip: Number of UE Groups included in this message. Value 0-8

Name: PDUType
ToolTip: 0: PRACH, 1: PUSCH,  2: PUCCH, 3: SRS

Name: PDUSize
ToolTip: Size of the PDU control information (in bytes). This length value includes the 4 bytes required for the PDU type and PDU size parameters. Value: 0 - 65535

Name: pduBitmap
ToolTip: Bitmap indicating presence of optional PDUs Bit 0: puschData (Indicates data is expected on the PUSCH) Bit 1:puschUci (Indicates UCI is expected on the PUSCH) Bit 2: puschPtrs (Indicates PTRS included (FR2)) Bit 3: dftsOfdm (Indicates DFT S-OFDM transmission)

Name: RNTI
ToolTip: The RNTI used for identifying the UE when receiving the PDU

Name: Handle
ToolTip: An opaque handling returned in the RxData.indication and/or UCI.indication message

Name: BWPsize
ToolTip: Number of contiguous PRBs allocated to the BWP, Value: 1-275

Name: BWPStart
ToolTip: Bandwidth part start RB index from reference CRB, Value: 0-274

Name: SubcarrierSpacing
ToolTip: Value:0-4

Name: CyclicPrefix
ToolTip: Cyclic prefix type, 0: Normal; 1: Extended

Name: targetCodeRate
ToolTip: Target coding rate [TS38.214 sec 6.1.4.1]. This is the number of information bits per 1024 coded bits expressed in 0.1 bit units

Name: qamModOrder
ToolTip: QAM modulation [TS38.214 sec 6.1.4.1] Value: 2,4,6,8

Name: mcsIndex
ToolTip: MCS index [TS38.214, sec 6.1.4.1], should match value sent in DCI Value : 0-31

Name: mcsTable
ToolTip: MCS-Table-PUSCH [TS38.214, sec 6.1.4.1] Value: 0: notqam256 [TS38.214, table 5.1.3.1-1] 1: qam256 [TS38.214, table 5.1.3.1-2] 2: qam64LowSE [TS38.214, table 5.1.3.1-3] 3: notqam256-withTransformPrecoding [TS38.214, table 6.1.4.1-1] 4: qam64LowSE-withTransformPrecoding [TS38.214, table 6.1.4.1-2]

Name: TransformPrecoding
ToolTip: Indicates if transform precoding is enabled or disabled [TS38.214, sec 6.1.4.1] [TS38.211 6.3.1.4] Value: 0: enabled, 1: disabled

Name: dataScramblingId
ToolTip: dataScramblingIdentityPdsch [TS38.211, sec 6.3.1.1] It equals the higher-layer parameter Datascrambling- Identity if configured and the RNTI equals the C-RNTI, otherwise L2 needs to set it to physical cell id. Value: 0-65535

Name: nrOfLayers
ToolTip: Number of layers [TS38.211, sec 6.3.1.3] Value : 1-4

Name: ulDmrsSymbPos
ToolTip: DMRS symbol positions [TS38.211, sec 6.4.1.1.3 and Tables 6.4.1.1.3-3 and 6.4.1.1.3-4] Bitmap occupying the 14 LSBs with: bit 0: first symbol and for each bit 0: no DMRS 1: DMRS

Name: dmrsConfigType
ToolTip: UL DMRS config type [TS38.211, sec 6.4.1.1.3], 0: type 1 1: type 2

Name: ulDmrsScramblingId
ToolTip: UL-DMRS-Scrambling-ID. If provided and the PUSCH is not a msg3 PUSCH, otherwise, L2 should set this to physical cell id. 0-65535

Name: SCID
ToolTip: DMRS sequence initialization [TS38.211, sec 6.4.1.1.1]. Should match what is sent in DCI 0_1, otherwise set to 0. Value : 0-1

Name: numDmrsCdmGrpsNoData
ToolTip: Number of DM-RS CDM groups without data [TS38.212 sec 7.3.1.1] Value: 1-3

Name: dmrsPorts
ToolTip: DMRS ports. [TS38.212 7.3.1.1.2] provides description between DCI 0-1 content and DMRS ports. Bitmap occupying the 11 LSBs with: bit 0: antenna port 1000 bit 11: antenna port 1011 and for each bit. 0: DMRS port not used 1: DMRS port used

Name: resourceAlloc
ToolTip: Resource Allocation Type [TS38.214, sec 6.1.2.2] 0: Type 0 1: Type 1.

Name: rbBitmap
ToolTip: For resource alloc type 0. [TS38.214, sec 6.1.2.2.1] [TS 38.212, 7.3.1.1.2] bitmap of RBs, 273 rounded up to multiple of 32. This bitmap is in units of VRBs. LSB of byte 0 of the bitmap represents the first RB of the BWP

Name: rbStart
ToolTip: For resource allocation type 1. [TS38.214, sec 6.1.2.2.2] The starting resource block within the BWP for this PUSCH. Value: 0-274.

Name: rbSize
ToolTip: For resource allocation type 1. [TS38.214, sec 6.1.2.2.2] The number of resource block within for this PUSCH. Value: 1-275

Name: VRBtoPRBMapping
ToolTip: VRB-to-PRB-mapping [TS38.211, sec 6.3.1.7] Value: 0: non-interleaved

Name: FrequencyHopping
ToolTip: For resource allocation type 1. [TS38.212, sec 7.3.1.1] [TS38.214, sec 6.3] Indicates if frequency hopping is enabled Value: 0: disabled 1: enabled

Name: txDirectCurrentLocation
ToolTip: The uplink Tx Direct Current location for the carrier. Only values in the value range of this field between 0 and 3299, which indicate the subcarrier index within the carrier corresponding to the numerology of the corresponding uplink BWP and value 3300, which indicates "Outside the carrier" and value 3301, which indicates "Undetermined position within the carrier" are used. [TS38.331, UplinkTxDirectCurrentBWP IE] Value: 0-4095

Name: uplinkFrequencyShift7p5khz
ToolTip: Indicates whether there is 7.5 kHz shift or not. [TS38.331, UplinkTxDirectCurrentBWP IE] Value: 0: false, 1: true

Name: StartSymbolIndex
ToolTip: Start symbol index of PUSCH mapping from the start of the slot, S. [TS38.214, Table 6.1.2.1-1] Value: 0-13

Name: NrOfSymbols
ToolTip: PUSCH duration in symbols, L [TS38.214, Table 6.1.2.1-1] Value: 1-14

Name: rvIndex
ToolTip: Redundancy version index [TS38.214, sec 6.1.4], it should match value sent in DCI Value : 0-3

Name: harqProcessID
ToolTip: HARQ process number [TS38.212, sec 7.3.1.1], it should match value sent in DCI Value: 0 -15

Name: newDataIndicator
ToolTip: Indicates if this new data or a retransmission [TS38.212, sec 7.3.1.1] Value: 0: retransmission 1: new data

Name: TBSize
ToolTip: Transmit block size (in bytes) [TS38.214 sec 6.1.4.2] Value: 0-65535

Name: numCb
ToolTip: Number of CBs in the TB (could be more than the number of CBs in this PUSCH transmission). Should be set to zero in any of the following conditions: 1) CBG is not supported 2) isReTx=0 (new transmission) 3) tbSize=0

Name: numPRGs
ToolTip: Number of PRGs spanning this allocation. Value : 1-275

Name: prgSize
ToolTip: Size in RBs of a precoding resource block group (PRG) – to which same precoding and digital beamforming gets applied. Value: 1-275
